{
  "id": "019cdcdc-fd01-7d11-b0d7-98cd073387d3",
  "content": "## Architecture\n\n### Crate placement\n\nAll RAG logic lives in `corvia-kernel`. Server layer (`corvia-server`) adds thin REST/MCP endpoints. Python SDK (M5) gets RAG for free via PyO3.\n\n\n### New files\n\n```\ncrates/corvia-kernel/src/\n  rag_pipeline.rs       — RagPipeline struct, context()/ask() orchestration\n  retriever.rs          — Retriever trait + VectorRetriever + GraphExpandRetriever\n  augmenter.rs          — Augmenter trait + StructuredAugmenter + TokenEstimator\n  rag_types.rs          — RetrievalOpts, TokenBudget, PipelineTrace, RagResponse, etc.\n\ncrates/corvia-common/src/\n  config.rs             — add RagConfig section\n\ncrates/corvia-server/src/\n  rest.rs               — add POST /v1/context, POST /v1/ask; fix search routing\n  mcp.rs                — add corvia_context, corvia_ask tools; fix search routing\n```\n",
  "source_version": "docs/rfcs/2026-03-02-m3.2-rag-pipeline-design.md",
